mechanoreception.notes: Sea cucumbers generally possess mechanoreceptors for detecting touch and pressure. Prevalence within Synallactidae is unknown based on the provided context.

chemoreception.notes: Sea cucumbers use chemoreception to locate food and mates. Prevalence within Synallactidae is unknown based on the provided context.

photoreception.notes: Some sea cucumbers possess rudimentary light-sensing abilities. Prevalence within Synallactidae is unknown based on the provided context.
